The paper discusses a methodology for analyzing the network of patents connected by citations, which involves clustering and predicting the temporal changes in the structure of the clusters. This involves the use of predictive analytics and could support policy decision making processes in science and technology. The paper does not explicitly mention any specific computer science sub-categories, but the techniques and methods used are relevant to several areas such as digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social networks (cs.SI), software engineering (cs.SD), and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
